cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper is about improving the architecture of feature pyramid networks for object detection using neural architecture search. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as neural architecture search, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence to improve object detection, which could also place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The paper also involves optimization techniques, which could place it in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category. Finally, the paper involves robotics applications, which could place it in the cs.RO (Robotics) category.
